Here, two different models are tried. First model is lm model and the second one is glm with family gamma and link function log. The lm model do not satisfy its conditions. Here, the mean of residuals are not zero and their variances seems not to be constant. To compare the full model with the glm model its AIC values is obtained. When it is compared to gamma model, it can be seen that the AIC value of the glm with gamma model is less. Also, different link functions for gamma family also tried and it is decided to use the glm model with family gamma and link function log.Later on, assumptions of the glm with family gamma also be investigated.

Part B¶

Here, glm model with binomial family (logistic regression) will be used. Because our response variable is a 0,1 variable.

To choose the right link function, we will investigate the logit and probit function considering AIC values. The results are almost the same but logit function tiny litte bit gave better AIC values. Therefore, the link function will be logit.
